1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:19,695
[no audio]

2
00:00:20,322 --> 00:00:45,161
[engines revving]

3
00:00:45,186 --> 00:00:50,175
[school bell rings]

4
00:00:50,200 --> 00:01:03,116
[indistinct murmuring]

5
00:01:03,141 --> 00:01:06,782
There is a distinct difference
between poetry and prose.

6
00:01:06,807 --> 00:01:11,818
Don, will you please stand and read
William Ernest Henley's poem on page 376?

7
00:01:13,720 --> 00:01:24,780
[pages turn]

8
00:01:33,901 --> 00:01:34,901
[book closes]

9
00:01:35,001 --> 00:01:36,001
[book slams down on desk]

10
00:01:36,302 --> 00:01:37,690
Poetry's dumb.

11
00:01:37,987 --> 00:01:41,241
[laughter]

12
00:01:41,874 --> 00:03:22,243
♪[instrumental music]♪

13
00:03:22,336 --> 00:03:23,570
Heh Donnie.

14
00:03:23,595 --> 00:03:26,013
-Wanna beer?
-Sure.

15
00:03:31,279 --> 00:03:33,192
So, why aren't you in school?

16
00:03:34,356 --> 00:03:35,716
- School's a waste.
- Yeah.

17
00:03:36,331 --> 00:03:37,451
Who needs it?

18
00:03:41,485 --> 00:03:43,614
Heh, Eddie here thinks he's
pretty fast with his hands.

19
00:03:43,639 --> 00:03:44,692
Oh yeah?

20
00:03:46,497 --> 00:03:47,628
No one beats me.

21
00:03:52,322 --> 00:03:53,389
No one beats me.

22
00:03:55,369 --> 00:03:56,670
Okay if I use just one hand?

23
00:03:57,025 --> 00:03:58,071
I'm holding a beer.

24
00:04:05,820 --> 00:04:06,887
[two hand slaps]

25
00:04:06,947 --> 00:04:07,948
Heh, wait a minute.[laughter]

26
00:04:07,948 --> 00:04:09,316
I wasn't ready.[laughter]

27
00:04:18,002 --> 00:04:19,654
[two hand slaps] 
Dang!

28
00:04:19,679 --> 00:04:22,729
[laughter] 
My eye.

29
00:04:22,754 --> 00:04:24,056
Just call me Mr. no one.

30
00:04:24,853 --> 00:04:25,887
How come?

31
00:04:26,154 --> 00:04:27,154
You said no one beats you.

32
00:04:27,179 --> 00:04:28,179
[laughter]

33
00:04:28,204 --> 00:04:29,371
Heh, reflexes don't mean nothin.

34
00:04:30,404 --> 00:04:31,672
I can still out ride you.

35
00:04:31,697 --> 00:04:32,775
Let's race and see.

36
00:04:32,873 --> 00:04:34,074
Sounds good.

37
00:04:34,708 --> 00:04:37,845
- Tonight at seven?
- No, now.

38
00:04:38,178 --> 00:04:40,000
Yeah Donnie, you can use my bike.

39
00:04:41,114 --> 00:04:42,716
Okay. Where?

40
00:04:42,716 --> 00:04:43,817
Here.

41
00:04:43,817 --> 00:04:45,652
- What about the stop sign?
- We run it.

42
00:04:46,019 --> 00:04:47,187
Unless you're scared.

43
00:04:47,588 --> 00:04:51,758
[chicken clucking]

44
00:04:52,559 --> 00:04:53,594
Let's do it.

45
00:04:53,854 --> 00:04:55,742
- Alright!
- Come on now. Let's do it!

46
00:04:55,851 --> 00:04:59,651
[engine starts up]
[engine revs up]

47
00:04:59,750 --> 00:05:10,864
[engine idles]

48
00:05:10,889 --> 00:05:17,933
[engine revs up]

49
00:05:17,958 --> 00:05:22,000
[engine idles]

50
00:05:22,155 --> 00:05:24,087
[barrel hits the street]
[engine revs]

51
00:05:24,391 --> 00:05:25,870
Alright, when this hits the ground,

52
00:05:25,948 --> 00:05:27,728
first one down and back here wins.

53
00:05:27,768 --> 00:05:30,531
[engines rev up]

54
00:05:32,766 --> 00:05:35,929
[engines roar]

55
00:05:35,954 --> 00:05:37,038
Wooh!

56
00:05:37,063 --> 00:05:38,853
[engines roar]

57
00:05:38,884 --> 00:05:41,190
[brakes screech]
[car horn blares]

58
00:05:41,229 --> 00:05:44,929
[engines roar]

59
00:05:44,954 --> 00:05:47,335
[tires screech]

60
00:05:47,368 --> 00:05:49,996
[engines hum]

61
00:05:50,022 --> 00:05:53,466
[engines roar]

62
00:05:53,491 --> 00:05:54,491
[thud]

63
00:05:54,516 --> 00:05:55,635
[engines roar]

64
00:05:55,660 --> 00:05:57,280
[truck's horn blares]

65
00:05:57,305 --> 00:05:58,485
Go! Go!

66
00:05:58,510 --> 00:06:03,272
[engines roar]

67
00:06:03,297 --> 00:06:04,386
Whooh!

68
00:06:04,411 --> 00:06:08,112
[engines roar by]
[engines fade]

69
00:06:14,514 --> 00:06:16,949
[engines trail off]

70
00:06:17,035 --> 00:06:19,229
[brakes screech]

71
00:06:19,268 --> 00:06:28,430
[engines hum]

72
00:06:28,455 --> 00:06:29,924
Good job Donnie.

73
00:06:29,924 --> 00:06:32,083
Yeah! Alright!
Yeah!

74
00:06:33,668 --> 00:06:34,801
Nice race Don.

75
00:06:38,086 --> 00:06:40,356
Hey, did you see your old man back there?
Nah.

76
00:06:40,381 --> 00:06:41,797
Think he saw you.

77
00:06:43,261 --> 00:06:44,543
Not as fast as I was going.

78
00:06:44,684 --> 00:06:46,067
[laughter] 
Still...

79
00:06:46,734 --> 00:06:48,702
I think you better
have a story for tonight.

80
00:06:50,132 --> 00:06:51,317
No problem.

81
00:06:51,685 --> 00:06:53,169
My old man only
knows what I tell him.

82
00:06:54,157 --> 00:06:55,189
I'll tell you what we'll do.

83
00:07:11,983 --> 00:07:13,370
I don't know what to do Emilio.

84
00:07:16,306 --> 00:07:17,362
Don's slipping away.

85
00:07:20,846 --> 00:07:22,018
I don't have any control.

86
00:07:23,753 --> 00:07:25,044
What does Don like to do?

87
00:07:26,819 --> 00:07:27,866
He likes motorcycles.

88
00:07:29,258 --> 00:07:30,318
Why don't you give him one?

89
00:07:32,299 --> 00:07:33,670
Give him a motorcycle?

90
00:07:35,027 --> 00:07:37,469
He is street racing and
cutting school now.

91
00:07:39,074 --> 00:07:40,076
I can't reward that.

92
00:07:40,861 --> 00:07:41,861
You don't.

93
00:07:42,510 --> 00:07:43,998
If he doesn't do what you want,

94
00:07:44,209 --> 00:07:46,063
you take away the motorcycle.

95
00:07:48,958 --> 00:07:49,995
Emilio.

96
00:07:50,965 --> 00:07:52,140
That's brilliant.

97
00:07:52,165 --> 00:07:54,096
[chuckles] 
Thank you for noticing.

98
00:07:54,824 --> 00:07:56,437
But I can't justgive it to him.

99
00:07:56,523 --> 00:08:00,487
No, you have to make sure that,
he thinks, he's earned it.

100
00:08:02,467 --> 00:08:03,819
That shouldn't be
too hard to do.

101
00:08:04,052 --> 00:08:06,757
[motorcycle outside]

102
00:08:09,900 --> 00:08:11,301
[door opens]

103
00:08:12,918 --> 00:08:14,481
[door closes]

104
00:08:14,773 --> 00:08:15,934
Where's your jacket?

105
00:08:18,138 --> 00:08:20,483
Oh I, uh, lent it to a friend.

106
00:08:21,491 --> 00:08:22,976
He had a motorcycle race today.

107
00:08:23,080 --> 00:08:24,088
Oh, I see.

108
00:08:24,387 --> 00:08:25,457
[knock at door]

109
00:08:26,552 --> 00:08:27,976
Must be him now.

110
00:08:28,702 --> 00:08:30,054
[door opens]

111
00:08:30,594 --> 00:08:32,798
- Mike, what's happening?
- Heh, Don.

112
00:08:34,004 --> 00:08:35,008
Hi Mr. Castro.

113
00:08:35,035 --> 00:08:36,559
Hello. [door closes]

114
00:08:36,911 --> 00:08:38,069
Look Don, I gotta go.

115
00:08:38,966 --> 00:08:40,013
Thanks for the jacket.

116
00:08:40,309 --> 00:08:41,349
Did you win the race?

117
00:08:43,098 --> 00:08:46,396
Nah, but it was close.

118
00:08:46,905 --> 00:08:49,640
I hear around town that
Don's a pretty good racer.

119
00:08:50,484 --> 00:08:51,806
He's the best.

120
00:08:52,624 --> 00:08:55,624
Oh, he can't be the best.

121
00:09:00,942 --> 00:09:02,206
Why can't I be?

122
00:09:02,231 --> 00:09:03,791
You're not racing at the track.

123
00:09:03,939 --> 00:09:06,076
Should I put a motor
on my bicycle to race?

124
00:09:06,138 --> 00:09:07,812
I'd buy a motorcycle for you.

125
00:09:08,265 --> 00:09:09,771
If that's all you needed.

126
00:09:10,697 --> 00:09:12,976
See you later.

127
00:09:13,772 --> 00:09:15,092
What do you think I need?

128
00:09:15,820 --> 00:09:16,949
You are just not good enough.

129
00:09:17,289 --> 00:09:18,527
I'm the best there is.

130
00:09:18,699 --> 00:09:21,115
You get a motorcycle
and I'll win every race.

131
00:09:21,159 --> 00:09:22,876
You got to be able to ride.

132
00:09:23,137 --> 00:09:24,550
I'll show you I can ride.

133
00:09:24,590 --> 00:09:26,308
You show me C's in school too.

134
00:09:27,367 --> 00:09:29,434
Or the wheels stop turning.

135
00:09:31,056 --> 00:09:32,214
I'll get the grades.

136
00:09:32,688 --> 00:09:35,313
You street race, and I
will sell the motorcycle.

137
00:09:37,297 --> 00:09:38,390
Okay.

138
00:09:39,024 --> 00:09:40,148
Do we have a deal?

139
00:09:43,347 --> 00:09:44,347
Deal.

140
00:09:56,781 --> 00:09:58,249
Where did you get that?

141
00:09:58,274 --> 00:10:00,334
Your grandfather took it in trade.

142
00:10:00,730 --> 00:10:01,752
Why?

143
00:10:02,303 --> 00:10:04,205
That's, one of life's mysteries.

144
00:10:06,435 --> 00:10:07,770
What are you going to do with it?

145
00:10:09,404 --> 00:10:10,514
It's for you.

146
00:10:12,414 --> 00:10:14,316
I didn't make a deal to join the circus.

147
00:10:15,099 --> 00:10:16,800
I thought you were going
to show me you could ride.

148
00:10:16,825 --> 00:10:18,225
Not a circus bike.

149
00:10:18,655 --> 00:10:20,879
For dirt bike racing, you need balance.

150
00:10:21,548 --> 00:10:25,097
- If you don't think you can do it.
- No. I can do it.

151
00:10:27,683 --> 00:10:28,817
We'll see.

152
00:10:31,384 --> 00:10:33,266
String these up between the
fences in the back yard.

153
00:10:34,332 --> 00:10:35,366
Why?

154
00:10:35,696 --> 00:10:37,508
Because, I don't want
you to break anything.

155
00:10:38,484 --> 00:10:39,752
I don't need this.

156
00:10:41,965 --> 00:10:43,200
Just put it up.

157
00:11:10,510 --> 00:11:11,812
Here you go.

158
00:11:28,462 --> 00:11:29,541
[thud]

159
00:11:32,415 --> 00:11:34,150
Maybe you should just quit.

160
00:11:35,878 --> 00:11:36,979
I'll ride it.

161
00:11:40,116 --> 00:11:41,284
Hi Don.

162
00:11:41,766 --> 00:11:43,230
I saw you from my window.

163
00:11:44,032 --> 00:11:45,300
What are you doing?

164
00:11:46,341 --> 00:11:49,869
I've got to show my dad I have balance
before he'll let me race motorcycles.

165
00:11:50,339 --> 00:11:52,041
Talk about dumb.

166
00:11:52,785 --> 00:11:56,147
This rope is another dumb idea of his.
It is not going to hold me up.

167
00:11:56,659 --> 00:11:58,028
Well, let me help.

168
00:11:59,771 --> 00:12:01,139
What's the matter?

169
00:12:01,366 --> 00:12:02,366
Nothing.

170
00:12:03,421 --> 00:12:04,822
You look different.

171
00:12:05,440 --> 00:12:07,058
What do you mean?

172
00:12:07,245 --> 00:12:09,636
Bigger, I mean taller.

173
00:12:09,850 --> 00:12:11,264
Well I grew an inch.

174
00:12:11,706 --> 00:12:13,194
Yeah, at least.

175
00:12:16,120 --> 00:12:19,349
- Put your arm on my shoulder.
- Sure.

176
00:12:21,201 --> 00:12:22,636
Got it.

177
00:12:25,494 --> 00:12:26,664
[thud]

178
00:12:29,818 --> 00:12:31,889
You want to try again?

179
00:12:33,354 --> 00:12:34,455
Sure.

180
00:12:34,480 --> 00:13:43,358
♪[inspirational music]♪

181
00:13:45,288 --> 00:13:46,423
I gotta go.

182
00:13:47,980 --> 00:13:49,282
I could use some help tomorrow.

183
00:13:50,502 --> 00:13:51,502
Okay.

184
00:13:55,987 --> 00:13:57,848
- Bye.
- Bye.

185
00:14:09,030 --> 00:14:10,331
Maybe I was wrong about you.

186
00:14:10,593 --> 00:14:12,195
What do you mean, maybe?

187
00:14:12,220 --> 00:14:14,045
You look like, maybe you can ride.

188
00:14:14,520 --> 00:14:15,659
I can ride.

189
00:14:15,684 --> 00:14:18,648
We'll have to get you a
motorcycle this week, to find out.

190
00:14:19,110 --> 00:14:22,347
- When do I race?
- In the Hollister Open, next month.

191
00:14:23,220 --> 00:14:25,914
- Alright.
- You did it.

192
00:14:27,253 --> 00:14:28,607
I'm so proud of you.

193
00:14:29,513 --> 00:14:31,414
Oh no problem with your credit
Mrs. Naygrow,

194
00:14:31,604 --> 00:14:33,446
I am buying a motorcycle for my son.

195
00:14:33,471 --> 00:14:36,595
And, I am asking everyone to pay cash,
for the deliveries this month.

196
00:14:38,857 --> 00:14:40,109
Thank you very much.

197
00:14:40,906 --> 00:14:42,219
I know just the bike I want Dad.

198
00:14:43,195 --> 00:14:44,899
I saw it over at Hollister Cycle.

199
00:14:45,286 --> 00:14:47,822
It's a 650 cc TT Special.

200
00:14:48,943 --> 00:14:51,384
- Brand new bike?
- It's a beauty.

201
00:14:51,987 --> 00:14:55,533
Would it be excellent, if we bought it?

202
00:14:56,402 --> 00:14:57,730
Yeah, it sure would be.

203
00:14:58,697 --> 00:15:02,053
Well, you're getting C's in school,
not A's.

204
00:15:02,759 --> 00:15:05,205
So, here's a fair bike.

205
00:15:24,079 --> 00:15:25,204
- Hi.
- Hi.

206
00:15:25,229 --> 00:15:26,229
Hey.

207
00:15:39,023 --> 00:15:40,882
How about me being your first rider?

208
00:15:41,191 --> 00:15:42,326
Sure, come on.

209
00:15:53,577 --> 00:18:16,031
♪[uplifting music]♪

210
00:18:30,500 --> 00:18:31,902
What a great feeling.

211
00:18:33,119 --> 00:18:34,621
Let me show you a better one.

212
00:18:41,966 --> 00:18:45,389
Why do you and your dad
yell at each other so much?

213
00:18:46,030 --> 00:18:47,331
Let's don't talk now.

214
00:18:52,081 --> 00:18:53,482
I want to get to know you better.

215
00:18:55,337 --> 00:18:56,371
It's personal.

216
00:18:58,996 --> 00:19:01,285
Well what you are doing
now is personal too.

217
00:19:03,081 --> 00:19:04,583
My old man don't care about me.

218
00:19:06,258 --> 00:19:08,060
Well, my parents care about me.

219
00:19:09,365 --> 00:19:11,727
But they never bought me
anything like this bike.

220
00:19:12,995 --> 00:19:14,113
He's always working.

221
00:19:14,255 --> 00:19:16,057
He never takes time to do things with me.

222
00:19:17,323 --> 00:19:20,648
Well maybe that say more about his
business than it does about him.

223
00:19:21,712 --> 00:19:23,116
Yeah, maybe.

224
00:19:24,696 --> 00:19:27,354
What happened to you at
school on Friday, anyway?

225
00:19:28,927 --> 00:19:30,429
We've talked enough.

226
00:19:32,398 --> 00:19:34,006
What happened Don?

227
00:19:35,182 --> 00:19:36,517
I don't like school.

228
00:19:37,667 --> 00:19:38,902
Well, why?

229
00:19:39,128 --> 00:19:40,496
I just don't like it!

230
00:19:42,153 --> 00:19:43,593
We've talked enough.

231
00:19:47,125 --> 00:19:48,495
Take me home.

232
00:19:59,516 --> 00:20:01,017
It's a package deal Don.

233
00:20:01,778 --> 00:20:03,819
My mind and my body go together.

234
00:20:04,134 --> 00:20:07,142
If you just want to feel good,
you can go and do that for yourself.

235
00:20:24,993 --> 00:20:26,295
Where have you been Tina?

236
00:20:27,993 --> 00:20:29,361
With Don Castro.

237
00:20:30,152 --> 00:20:31,453
Why were you with him?

238
00:20:34,298 --> 00:20:35,641
I don't know.

239
00:20:39,527 --> 00:21:27,660
♪[contemplative music]♪

240
00:21:27,718 --> 00:21:28,718
[phone rings]

241
00:21:29,630 --> 00:21:30,630
[phone rings]

242
00:21:31,783 --> 00:21:32,783
[phone rings]

243
00:21:32,808 --> 00:21:33,842
Tina: Hello?

244
00:21:34,869 --> 00:21:37,405
I'll be in the garage,
if you want to talk.

245
00:21:38,149 --> 00:21:39,150
Okay.

246
00:21:39,339 --> 00:21:48,105
♪[contemplative music]♪

247
00:21:48,239 --> 00:21:49,239
Hi.

248
00:21:49,684 --> 00:21:50,684
Hi.

249
00:21:53,507 --> 00:21:54,944
I'm sorry about today.

250
00:21:55,825 --> 00:21:56,825
It's okay.

251
00:22:01,620 --> 00:22:03,261
No, I'm not sorry I tried.

252
00:22:04,988 --> 00:22:06,323
I'm sorry you didn't want to.

253
00:22:07,176 --> 00:22:08,310
Go all the way?

254
00:22:09,540 --> 00:22:10,540
Yeah.

255
00:22:11,587 --> 00:22:13,158
So...

256
00:22:15,087 --> 00:22:19,455
if I had let you, what would
it have meant to you?

257
00:22:21,583 --> 00:22:22,865
What should it mean?

258
00:22:23,076 --> 00:22:24,493
Well, that you love me,

259
00:22:25,054 --> 00:22:28,062
and that you would someday want me
to marry you, and have your baby.

260
00:22:30,370 --> 00:22:31,771
That's pretty serious.

261
00:22:33,257 --> 00:22:35,126
I think that's how it should be.

262
00:22:37,146 --> 00:22:38,531
I'm not ready for that.

263
00:22:39,265 --> 00:22:40,429
Me either.

264
00:22:44,617 --> 00:22:46,755
You're the only one who has
ever wanted to get to know me.

265
00:22:53,542 --> 00:22:56,009
That's because I like you Don.

266
00:23:00,439 --> 00:23:01,919
I like you too, Tina.

267
00:23:07,586 --> 00:23:08,586
Maybe...

268
00:23:11,394 --> 00:23:13,347
instead of going all the way...

269
00:23:15,713 --> 00:23:17,356
we could go a quarter of the way.

270
00:23:18,817 --> 00:23:19,987
Maybe.

271
00:23:22,533 --> 00:23:25,101
You never told me why
you don't like school.

272
00:23:29,400 --> 00:23:30,867
I don't like school...

273
00:23:33,532 --> 00:23:35,063
because I am not that good at it.

274
00:23:36,018 --> 00:23:37,136
Why not?

275
00:23:48,138 --> 00:23:49,406
I can't read.

276
00:23:51,442 --> 00:23:52,575
Not at all?

277
