Castro pushing for all he's worth.

780
00:57:41,825 --> 00:57:43,868
White flag, one more lap to go.

781
00:57:43,893 --> 00:57:47,154
It's Don Castro followed by
Stan Morris, Mark Butler,

782
00:57:47,179 --> 00:57:50,213
then it's John Eichelbaugh
and Jerry Johnson.

783
00:57:50,424 --> 00:57:53,229
It's Don Castro, wide to the outside.

784
00:57:53,281 --> 00:57:59,281
♪[inspirational music]♪

785
00:57:59,350 --> 00:58:02,901
Don Castro your leader,
on number 203, a borrowed bike.

786
00:58:02,948 --> 00:58:07,034
Takes it back, one more time Castro
heading into the turn.

787
00:58:07,159 --> 00:58:16,554
♪[inspirational music]♪

788
00:58:16,766 --> 00:58:20,186
Don Castro had a blow out on his
own bike up on this corner.

789
00:58:20,211 --> 00:58:22,605
It comes to the checkered flag.

790
00:58:22,630 --> 00:58:24,395
It's Don Castro!

791
00:58:24,435 --> 00:58:29,328
Followed by Mark Butler, Stan Morris,
Scott Eichelbaugh,

792
00:58:29,353 --> 00:58:31,629
Jerry Johnson, John Eichelbaugh.

793
00:58:31,654 --> 00:58:35,118
[cheering]

794
00:58:57,323 --> 00:58:58,491
Tina.

795
00:59:14,543 --> 00:59:15,844
You want me to talk to them?

796
00:59:17,251 --> 00:59:18,251
No.

797
00:59:20,257 --> 00:59:21,310
We'll work it out.

798
00:59:23,913 --> 00:59:25,512
[cartoon noises]

799
00:59:25,722 --> 00:59:26,722
[chuckling]

800
00:59:30,987 --> 00:59:35,035
[cartoon noises]

801
00:59:35,060 --> 00:59:36,247
[chuckling]

802
00:59:39,104 --> 00:59:40,393
[chuckling]

803
00:59:41,743 --> 00:59:42,952
I don't understand, son.

804
00:59:44,533 --> 00:59:45,728
Your ankle's broken.

805
00:59:46,935 --> 00:59:48,013
Your bike is totaled.

806
00:59:49,761 --> 00:59:50,993
And you are not depressed?

807
00:59:53,084 --> 00:59:54,335
Because I know I'm good.

808
00:59:55,425 --> 00:59:58,035
No, not good.. great 
at racing motorcycles.

809
00:59:59,373 --> 01:00:00,641
I'll have my day.

810
01:00:01,931 --> 01:00:03,262
Can you do some
shopping for me?

811
01:00:03,458 --> 01:00:05,310
Sure. What do you need?

812
01:00:05,743 --> 01:00:06,991
A hacksaw... [taps cast]

813
01:00:08,464 --> 01:00:10,355
and the largest pair
of boots you can find.

814
01:00:10,595 --> 01:00:11,796
You sure you want to do that?

815
01:00:12,515 --> 01:00:14,168
You can't get the most out of racing...

816
01:00:15,031 --> 01:00:16,533
without putting the most in.

817
01:00:19,157 --> 01:00:20,725
I'm sure glad you're my son.

818
01:00:23,790 --> 01:00:24,790
Me too.

819
01:00:26,683 --> 01:00:28,085
Race announcer: Here at
the Columbus half mile,

820
01:00:28,110 --> 01:00:30,669
it's a win for Don Castro,
followed by Butler..

821
01:00:30,694 --> 01:00:37,871
[engines]

822
01:00:37,952 --> 01:00:41,302
Race announcer: It's a great afternoon,
for the win it's Don Castro,

823
01:00:41,327 --> 01:00:42,572
followed by Butler.

824
01:00:42,597 --> 01:00:48,335
[engines]

825
01:00:48,421 --> 01:00:54,148
Race announcer: Giving us all a
pull off win it's Don Castro!

826
01:00:55,566 --> 01:02:06,012
♪[uplifting music]♪

827
01:02:06,077 --> 01:02:07,118
[joyful laugh]

828
01:02:07,150 --> 01:02:19,515
♪[uplifting music]♪

829
01:02:20,788 --> 01:02:21,788
Great Dad.

830
01:02:23,338 --> 01:02:24,338
Leave a note.

831
01:02:29,716 --> 01:02:30,716
Dear son.

832
01:02:32,259 --> 01:02:33,259
This...

833
01:02:35,224 --> 01:02:36,904
motorcycle...

834
01:02:38,027 --> 01:02:40,163
is "rof",

835
01:02:41,291 --> 01:02:42,291
for

836
01:02:42,586 --> 01:02:44,618
This motorcycle is for...

837
01:02:45,922 --> 01:02:46,922
you're...

838
01:02:47,745 --> 01:02:48,745
A...

839
01:02:49,733 --> 01:02:50,733
in...

840
01:02:51,546 --> 01:02:52,546
English.

841
01:02:53,348 --> 01:02:54,348
I'm...

842
01:02:54,476 --> 01:02:55,476
sure...

843
01:02:57,696 --> 01:03:00,968
"droup".. of.. you.

844
01:03:06,457 --> 01:03:07,592
Yeah.

845
01:03:07,743 --> 01:03:10,472
[school bell rings]

846
01:03:11,272 --> 01:03:14,019
Alright people, let's not forget,
we have a test tomorrow.

847
01:03:14,044 --> 01:03:15,997
[groans]

848
01:03:17,516 --> 01:03:19,171
Don, would you
please stay a moment?

849
01:03:23,180 --> 01:03:24,314
Please, sit down.

850
01:03:29,386 --> 01:03:30,920
What word do you see here Don?

851
01:03:34,642 --> 01:03:35,642
Saw.

852
01:03:39,134 --> 01:03:40,502
And what word it this?

853
01:03:43,823 --> 01:03:44,823
Dog.

854
01:03:47,558 --> 01:03:49,058
You're not dumb, Don.

855
01:03:51,332 --> 01:03:52,533
What's wrong with me?

856
01:03:52,642 --> 01:03:54,010
You have dyslexia.

857
01:03:55,137 --> 01:03:56,272
What does that mean?

858
01:03:56,544 --> 01:03:59,253
It means the circuits of your
brain don't always connect.

859
01:03:59,653 --> 01:04:01,188
So, reading is hard for you.

860
01:04:01,632 --> 01:04:02,666
Is there a cure?

861
01:04:02,896 --> 01:04:03,896
No.

862
01:04:09,177 --> 01:04:11,310
Now that you have told me this,
am I supposed to feel better?

863
01:04:11,504 --> 01:04:13,746
Well, is should be nice
to know you're not dumb.

864
01:04:13,873 --> 01:04:14,874
Not dumb...

865
01:04:16,186 --> 01:04:17,521
just defective.

866
01:04:18,988 --> 01:04:22,254
There is one advantage,
if you continue racing.

867
01:04:22,412 --> 01:04:23,614
How did you know I raced?

868
01:04:23,639 --> 01:04:25,863
Women read the sports section too, Don.

869
01:04:26,080 --> 01:04:29,150
At high speeds, race car
drivers who have dyslexia,

870
01:04:29,191 --> 01:04:31,360
claim they see things in slow motion.

871
01:04:31,401 --> 01:04:32,401
How is that good?

872
01:04:32,483 --> 01:04:35,274
Well, you'll have more time to
react than your competitors.

873
01:04:35,606 --> 01:04:37,975
So, you'll be able to go faster.

874
01:04:38,060 --> 01:04:39,260
I've never had that happen.

875
01:04:39,325 --> 01:04:42,096
Have you ever raced on a mile
track like the race cars do?

876
01:04:44,061 --> 01:04:45,061
No.

877
01:04:47,036 --> 01:04:48,174
Are you gonna fail me?

878
01:04:51,789 --> 01:04:53,673
I'm, going to give you a C.

879
01:05:03,622 --> 01:05:05,270
I'm sorry I walked out of your class.

880
01:05:06,044 --> 01:05:07,563
I understand, Don.

881
01:05:10,251 --> 01:05:11,258
Thank you for your help.

882
01:05:12,852 --> 01:05:13,852
Dad.

883
01:05:14,061 --> 01:05:15,061
Yeah.

884
01:05:15,314 --> 01:05:16,582
Can you help me with this carburetor?

885
01:05:18,844 --> 01:05:20,464
I've got some deliveries
to make today, Don.

886
01:05:21,230 --> 01:05:22,230
Oh.

887
01:05:24,662 --> 01:05:25,730
Tell you what...

888
01:05:26,854 --> 01:05:28,222
I'll help you, if you help me.

889
01:05:29,092 --> 01:05:30,092
Okay.

890
01:05:42,726 --> 01:05:43,726
Dad.

891
01:05:45,256 --> 01:05:46,624
How'd you like to be my partner?

892
01:05:47,658 --> 01:05:48,726
What in?

893
01:05:49,119 --> 01:05:50,320
Motorcycle racing.

894
01:05:51,248 --> 01:05:52,540
I was your partner already.

895
01:05:58,112 --> 01:06:01,415
Yeah, but you are putting everything in,

896
01:06:01,440 --> 01:06:02,990
and I'm getting all the benefit.

897
01:06:04,674 --> 01:06:05,872
I wouldn't say that.

898
01:06:07,002 --> 01:06:08,336
All the money you spent.

899
01:06:08,732 --> 01:06:11,493
The time driving me to the races,
being my mechanic.

900
01:06:12,684 --> 01:06:13,684
I'm the one...

901
01:06:15,350 --> 01:06:16,746
who gets to watch his son.

902
01:06:21,749 --> 01:06:23,411
I didn't get that A in English Dad.

903
01:06:25,448 --> 01:06:28,073
And, I want to pay you back for the
motorcycle with my prize money.

904
01:06:29,375 --> 01:06:31,669
- And then split the money I win with you.
- You didn't get the A?

905
01:06:39,136 --> 01:06:40,136
No.

906
01:06:43,072 --> 01:06:44,391
Why did you tell me this now?

907
01:06:48,816 --> 01:06:50,222
I didn't want to live a lie with you.

908
01:07:00,700 --> 01:07:01,948
I'm glad you told me.

909
01:07:05,741 --> 01:07:06,741
Partner.

910
01:07:10,556 --> 01:08:10,978
♪[soft music]♪

911
01:08:11,440 --> 01:08:12,842
That wasn't so bad.

912
01:08:13,814 --> 01:08:15,349
The first load never is.

913
01:08:15,512 --> 01:09:08,244
♪[soft music]♪

914
01:09:08,572 --> 01:09:09,823
This is our fourth load.

915
01:09:10,894 --> 01:09:11,894
Is this it?

916
01:09:14,220 --> 01:09:15,290
Not quite.

917
01:09:15,436 --> 01:09:22,376
♪[soft music]♪

918
01:09:22,592 --> 01:09:23,860
Is it always like this?

919
01:09:25,389 --> 01:09:26,389
No.

920
01:09:27,169 --> 01:09:29,105
Most days I make more loads.

921
01:09:30,807 --> 01:09:32,575
How long are you going to
keep working this hard?

922
01:09:35,678 --> 01:09:36,979
When your grandfather had his stroke,

923
01:09:38,504 --> 01:09:42,017
I told myself, I would help out for
six months, until he could handle it.

924
01:09:42,822 --> 01:09:44,096
And here I am.

925
01:09:44,322 --> 01:09:45,628
That was seven years ago.

926
01:09:47,835 --> 01:09:49,270
Do you like what you're doing?

927
01:09:50,093 --> 01:09:51,577
Like being my own boss.

928
01:09:52,951 --> 01:09:54,686
What are you gonna do
when you stop racing?

929
01:09:58,412 --> 01:09:59,446
I don't know.

930
01:10:00,293 --> 01:10:03,763
You better decide, or the
choice gets made for you.

931
01:10:12,543 --> 01:10:13,745
Well, you're all ready son.

932
01:10:15,252 --> 01:10:16,490
Better get some sleep.

933
01:10:17,822 --> 01:10:19,785
I'm gonna groove the tire
for traction, first.

934
01:10:20,308 --> 01:10:22,331
Okay. Good night.

935
01:10:25,620 --> 01:10:26,836
Good night Dad.

936
01:10:32,736 --> 01:10:33,863
[cheering]

937
01:10:34,151 --> 01:10:36,151
[distant] Race announcer: Castro,
down on the inside route.

938
01:10:36,206 --> 01:10:41,480
They come out of four and
it's, Castro, Mertins..

939
01:10:41,640 --> 01:10:45,210
At turn one, it's Don Castro, Tim Mertins.

940
01:10:45,841 --> 01:10:47,068
Don Castro's won it!

941
01:10:47,093 --> 01:10:50,241
[cheering]

942
01:10:52,769 --> 01:10:58,954
Thank you, for taking the time from
your busy schedule to come and see me.

943
01:10:58,979 --> 01:11:00,280
It is my pleasure, Mr. Iuno.

944
01:11:00,731 --> 01:11:06,383
Our company has benefited from your
past leadership in America, Mr. Igetsu.

945
01:11:06,863 --> 01:11:08,331
You are too kind, Mr. Iuno.

946
01:11:08,589 --> 01:11:10,124
Our motorcycles sell themselves.

947
01:11:11,776 --> 01:11:13,545
Oh no, Mr. Igetsu.

948
01:11:18,714 --> 01:11:23,091
As you can see, our
motorcycles sales move,

949
01:11:23,116 --> 01:11:26,226
with the winning of our
motorcycles in races.

950
01:11:32,987 --> 01:11:36,057
America loves winners, Mr. Igetsu.

951
01:11:36,724 --> 01:11:37,825
Yes, Mr. Iuno.

952
01:11:38,736 --> 01:11:41,094
Our company loves to win.

953
01:11:42,753 --> 01:11:44,054
Yes, Mr. Iuno.

954
01:11:44,788 --> 01:11:46,323
Who is Don Castro?

955
01:11:47,337 --> 01:11:48,672
He is new to the racing circuit.

956
01:11:50,713 --> 01:11:52,062
An independent?

957
01:11:52,540 --> 01:11:53,708
Yes, Mr. Iuno.

958
01:11:53,965 --> 01:11:57,941
He has won four races in a row,
with a broken ankle.

959
01:11:58,214 --> 01:11:59,886
- Yes, but he has never won--
- Perhaps...

960
01:12:00,620 --> 01:12:03,912
Mr. Castro should join our racing team.

961
01:12:04,313 --> 01:12:06,133
We have four good
riders now, Mr. Iuno.

962
01:12:06,832 --> 01:12:08,801
Good is winning, Mr. Igetsu.

963
01:12:09,426 --> 01:12:14,875
Our company, holds you personally
responsible to keep winning for America.

964
01:12:16,316 --> 01:12:17,418
Yes, Mr. Iuno.

965
01:12:24,921 --> 01:12:26,223
Where are you going?

966
01:12:26,967 --> 01:12:29,700
[whispers] Hi Tina.
I'm going to Sacramento.

967
01:12:30,767 --> 01:12:31,969
Why are you whispering?

968
01:12:34,264 --> 01:12:35,932
[whispers] I don't want
your parents to hear me.

969
01:12:36,669 --> 01:12:37,970
That's not funny.

970
01:12:38,274 --> 01:12:41,013
[whispers] I know Tina. It's sad.

971
01:12:50,782 --> 01:12:52,150
[whispers] When can I see you?

972
01:12:54,369 --> 01:12:55,804
I don't know.

973
01:13:08,173 --> 01:13:09,625
We'll be home around ten.

974
01:13:10,228 --> 01:13:11,869
Come out your window and
meet me in the garage.

975
01:13:13,778 --> 01:13:15,480
I'm tired of sneaking Don.

976
01:13:15,816 --> 01:13:17,201
What else can we do?

977
01:13:20,250 --> 01:13:21,552
I gotta go.

978
01:13:24,275 --> 01:13:25,650
Try to make it tonight.

979
01:13:25,878 --> 01:13:27,313
Okay, I'll try.

980
01:13:30,280 --> 01:13:31,925
I wish I was going with you.

981
01:13:32,914 --> 01:13:33,914
Me too.

982
01:13:42,050 --> 01:15:05,264
♪[contemplative music]♪

983
01:15:05,295 --> 01:15:06,900
Can I borrow the car, Mom?

984
01:15:07,244 --> 01:15:08,244
No, Tina.

985
01:15:13,814 --> 01:15:15,796
I have to have the car.

986
01:15:16,078 --> 01:15:18,314
- Tina, I don--
- Mom.

987
01:15:20,432 --> 01:15:22,018
I need the car.

988
01:15:24,800 --> 01:15:26,168
I really need it.

989
01:15:33,563 --> 01:15:35,734
The keys are in my purse.

990
01:15:39,057 --> 01:15:40,135
Thanks Mom.

991
01:15:53,500 --> 01:15:55,001
I love him, Dad.

992
01:15:56,627 --> 01:15:58,541
You don't know what love is Tina.

993
01:16:01,802 --> 01:16:06,566
Extra, extra, read all about it!
Tina loves Don!

994
01:16:13,974 --> 01:16:15,483
What's wrong with her?

995
01:16:16,272 --> 01:16:17,876
Where's she going?

996
01:16:18,273 --> 01:16:21,724
Race Announcer: And there's the
finish of the last chance qualifier..

997
01:16:21,780 --> 01:16:25,744
[announcer][engines] 
♪[upbeat music]♪

998
01:16:25,769 --> 01:16:30,100
Transferring to the feature
here, at the Sacramento Mile.

999
01:16:30,125 --> 01:16:33,883
It's been a flurry of activity,
this afternoon, here at the mile.

1000
01:16:33,908 --> 01:16:37,716
Tuners, riders, mechanics all
in there working on the bikes.

1001
01:16:37,771 --> 01:16:41,519
No one has been able to find just the
right piece of gearing, the right setup,

1002
01:16:41,552 --> 01:16:43,158
for this particular track.

1003
01:16:43,183 --> 01:16:45,516
Warm afternoon, seems to
be bringing the sand up.

1004
01:16:45,541 --> 01:16:48,271
This is definitely not a
race, fit for the dirt track,

1005
01:16:48,310 --> 01:16:50,872
as the moisture seems to have gone away.

1006
01:16:50,897 --> 01:16:52,818
We've got some top runners here.

1007
01:16:52,880 --> 01:16:57,890
[announcer] [engines] 
♪[upbeat music]♪

1008
01:16:57,915 --> 01:17:00,789
Looks like now they're going with
everything they can, the gearing.

1009
01:17:00,814 --> 01:17:02,835
That's what the backup motorcycle is for.

1010
01:17:02,860 --> 01:17:07,863
Changes in setup as they get set and ready
to come out for today's feature event.

1011
01:17:07,927 --> 01:17:10,790
It's been an incredible afternoon of
people searching for the right thing.

1012
01:17:11,024 --> 01:17:34,226
[announcer] [engines] 
♪[upbeat music]♪

1013
01:17:34,251 --> 01:17:36,256
Race announcer: ..unless they
change something drastic.

1014
01:17:36,281 --> 01:17:38,924
One rider though, who has
definitely got this dialed in,

1015
01:17:38,949 --> 01:17:43,463
Don Castro and his tuner
father, all the way from Hollister.

1016
01:17:43,488 --> 01:17:44,923
They've had an incredible year.

1017
01:17:44,948 --> 01:17:46,950
This is the first time
Castro has been on the mile.

1018
01:17:47,017 --> 01:17:50,721
He has qualified for the pole
position, with the track record

1019
01:17:50,746 --> 01:17:54,475
and he's got four major victories in
the last four races of this season.

1020
01:17:54,500 --> 01:17:57,310
So, as we go down here for the
season finale in Sacramento,

1021
01:17:57,328 --> 01:17:59,801
we are going to be looking
for a lot from this young man.

1022
01:17:59,826 --> 01:18:02,610
He really looks like he is a
promising rider on the way up,

1023
01:18:02,635 --> 01:18:04,704
and going to give us
a great thrill today.

1024
01:18:04,729 --> 01:18:07,609
As Castro and the other riders
get set and ready to come out,

1025
01:18:07,634 --> 01:18:09,775
in this afternoon's feature,
the season finale.

1026
01:18:09,813 --> 01:18:12,355
It looks like the greaser
got a new motorcycle.

1027
01:18:13,012 --> 01:18:14,012
Well...

1028
01:18:16,916 --> 01:18:21,331
nothing, beats the tiger in the tank.

1029
01:18:21,902 --> 01:18:24,433
[sinister laughter]

1030
01:18:25,418 --> 01:19:15,530
[announcer] [engines] 
♪[upbeat music]♪

1031
01:19:15,555 --> 01:19:18,848
Race announcer: On the pole, it's the
new rider, number 11, Dan Castro

1032
01:19:18,873 --> 01:19:29,103
[announcer] [engines] 
♪[upbeat music]♪

1033
01:19:29,128 --> 01:19:32,152
The finale, this evening, is
about ready to get underway.

1034
01:19:33,009 --> 01:19:35,526
[engines roar]

1035
01:19:35,730 --> 01:19:39,308
[announcer] [engines] 
♪[upbeat music]♪

1036
01:19:39,340 --> 01:19:42,850
Don Castro, down on the inside. Right
